Prior to installing LiBELa, some usual libraries and compilers must be present:

zlib (in Ubuntu systems, use the command "sudo apt-get install zlib1g-dev");
gcc and g++;

The install script will automatically compile the following libraries:

* gsl-1.16 (see http://www.gnu.org/software/gsl)
* nlopt-2.4.2 (see http://ab-initio.mit.edu/wiki/index.php/NLopt)
* openbabel-2.3.2 (see http://openbabel.org/wiki/Main_Page)

Afterwards, LiBELa will be compiled.

